<TEI.2><text><body><div1 type="alphabetic letter" n="C" org="uniform" sample="complete"><entryFree key="Cato" type="main" opt="n"><orth extent="full" opt="n">Cato,</orth> ancient Roman, celebrated for his virtue: <bibl n="shak. mv 1.1.166" default="NO" valid="yes">Merch. I, 1, 166</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. cor 1.4.57" default="NO" valid="yes">Cor. I, 4, 57</bibl> (O. Edd. <cit><quote>Calues).</quote> <bibl n="shak. jc 2.1.295" default="NO" valid="yes">Caes. II, 1, 295</bibl></cit>. <bibl n="shak. jc 5.1.101" default="NO" valid="yes">V, 1, 101</bibl>. His son: <bibl n="shak. jc 5.3.107" default="NO" valid="yes">Caes. V, 3, 107</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. jc 5.4.4" default="NO" valid="yes">V, 4, 4</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. jc 5.4.4" default="NO" valid="yes">V, 4, 4</bibl>
</entryFree></div1></body></text></TEI.2>